330 North Wabash.label: 330 North Wabash

Nan Madol.label: Nan Madol

Nisqually Entrance Historic District.label: Nisqually Entrance Historic District
Nisqually Entrance Historic District.description: The Nisqually Entrance Historic District comprises the first public entrance to Mount Rainier National Park. Wikipedia

1935 Labor Day hurricane.label: 1935 Labor Day hurricane
1935 Labor Day hurricane.description: The 1935 Labor Day Hurricane was the strongest tropical cyclone of the 1935 Atlantic hurricane season, and the most intense hurricane to make landfall in the United States and the Atlantic Basin in recorded history. Wikipedia

Portland Observatory.label: Portland Observatory
Portland Observatory.description: The Portland Observatory, built in 1807 at Portland, Maine, is the last surviving maritime signal tower in the United States. Wikipedia

Giant's Causeway.label: Giant's Causeway
Giant's Causeway.description:
The Giant's Causeway is an area of about 40,000 interlocking basalt columns, the result of an ancient volcanic eruption.

Puget Sound Naval Shipyard and Intermedi.label: Puget Sound Naval Shipyard and Intermediate Maintenance Facility
Puget Sound Naval Shipyard and Intermedi.description: Puget Sound Naval Shipyard and Intermediate Maintenance Facility is a United States Navy shipyard covering 179 acres on Puget Sound at Bremerton, Washington. Wikipedia

Kahoolawe.label: Kaho‘olawe

Visoki Dečani.label: Visoki Dečani
Visoki Dečani.description: Visoki Dečani is a major Serbian Orthodox Christian monastery located in Deçan, Kosovo. The monastic katholikon is the largest medieval church in the Balkans containing the most extensive preserved fresco decoration. Wikipedia

Alabama State University Historic Distri.label: Alabama State University Historic District
Alabama State University Historic Distri.description: The Alabama State University Historic District is a 26-acre historic district at the heart of the Alabama State University campus in Montgomery, Alabama. Wikipedia

Arecibo Observatory.label: Arecibo Observatory
Arecibo Observatory.description: The Arecibo Observatory is a radio telescope in the municipality of Arecibo, Puerto Rico. This observatory is operated by SRI International, USRA and UMET, under cooperative agreement with the National Science Foundation. Wikipedia

Annie Russell Theatre.label: Annie Russell Theatre
Annie Russell Theatre.description: The Annie Russell Theatre is a historic theater in Winter Park, Florida, United States. The theatre was named after the English-born actress Annie Russell. Wikipedia

Balboa Pavilion.label: Balboa Pavilion
Balboa Pavilion.description: The Balboa Pavilion in Newport Beach, Orange County, California, is a California Historical Landmark and a National Historic Place. Wikipedia

Adelbert Hall.label: Adelbert Hall
Adelbert Hall.description: Adelbert Hall is an administration building at Case Western Reserve University in Cleveland, Ohio and a registered historic building, listed in the National Register on 1973-10-30. Wikipedia
Architectural styles: Queen Anne Style architecture (Great Britain & Australia)

Balmoral Castle.label: Balmoral Castle
Balmoral Castle.description: Balmoral Castle is a large estate house in Royal Deeside, Aberdeenshire, Scotland. It is located near the village of Crathie, 6.2 miles west of Ballater and 6.8 miles east of Braemar. Wikipedia

Blair Castle.label: Blair Castle
Blair Castle.description: Blair Castle stands in its grounds near the village of Blair Atholl in Perthshire in Scotland. It is the ancestral home of the Clan Murray, and was historically the seat of their chief, the Duke of ... Wikipedia

Cawdor Castle.label: Cawdor Castle
Cawdor Castle.description: Cawdor Castle is set amid gardens in the parish of Cawdor, approximately 10 miles east of Inverness and 5 miles southwest of Nairn in Scotland. The castle is built around a 15th-century tower house, with substantial additions in later centuries. Wikipedia

Cemetery Ridge.label: Cemetery Ridge
Cemetery Ridge.description: Cemetery Ridge is a geographic feature in Gettysburg National Military Park, south of the town of Gettysburg, Pennsylvania, that figured prominently in the Battle of Gettysburg, July 1 to July 3, 1863. Wikipedia

College Hill Town Hall.label: College Hill Town Hall
College Hill Town Hall.description:
College Hill Town Hall is a registered historic building in Cincinnati, Ohio, listed in the National Register on March 17, 1978.
It was historically used as a city hall. Wikipedia

Corcoran Gallery of Art.label: Corcoran College of Art and Design
Corcoran Gallery of Art.description: The Corcoran College of Art and Design, founded in 1890, is the only professional college of art and design in Washington, D.C., United States, located in the Downtown area. Wikipedia

Dunvegan Castle.label: Dunvegan Castle
Dunvegan Castle.description: Dunvegan Castle is a castle a mile and a half to the north of Dunvegan on the Isle of Skye, situated off the West coast of Scotland. It is the seat of the MacLeod of MacLeod, chief of the Clan MacLeod. Wikipedia

Eastern Columbia Building.label: Eastern Columbia Building
Eastern Columbia Building.description: The Eastern Columbia Building is a thirteen-story building located at 849 S. Broadway in the Broadway Theater District of downtown Los Angeles and is considered by many to be the most beautiful of Los ... Wikipedia

Frederick Ayer Mansion.label: Frederick Ayer Mansion
Frederick Ayer Mansion.description: The Frederick Ayer Mansion is a National Historic Landmark on 395 Commonwealth Avenue in Boston, Massachusetts. Wikipedia

Grand Concourse (Bronx).label: Grand Concourse
Grand Concourse (Bronx).description: The Grand Concourse is a major thoroughfare in the borough of the Bronx in New York City. It was designed by Louis Aloys Risse, an Alsatian immigrant who had previously worked for the New York Central ... Wikipedia

Gropius House.label: Gropius House
Gropius House.description: The Gropius House was the family residence of noted architect Walter Gropius at 68 Baker Bridge Road, Lincoln, Massachusetts. It is a National Historic Landmark, owned by Historic New England, and is open to the public. Wikipedia

Grosvenor Museum.label: Grosvenor Museum
Grosvenor Museum.description: Grosvenor Museum is in Grosvenor Street, Chester, Cheshire, England. It is designated by English Heritage as a Grade II listed building. Wikipedia

Hildene.label: Hildene
Hildene.description: Hildene, The Lincoln Family Home located in Manchester in the U.S. state of Vermont, was the summer home of Robert Todd Lincoln and his wife Mary Harlan Lincoln. Wikipedia

Huntington Building.label: Huntington Bank Building
Huntington Building.description: The Huntington Bank Building is a high-rise office building on Euclid Avenue in downtown Cleveland, Ohio. Wikipedia

John Waterman Arnold House.label: John Waterman Arnold House
John Waterman Arnold House.description:
John Waterman Arnold House is an historic house at 11 Roger Williams Avenue in Warwick, Rhode Island.
The house was added to the National Historic Register in 1971. Wikipedia

Leighton House Museum.label: Leighton House Museum
Leighton House Museum.description:
The Leighton House Museum is a museum in the Holland Park district of Kensington and Chelsea in London.
The former home of the painter Frederic, Lord Leighton, it has been open to the public since 1929. Wikipedia

Lower Lake Stone Jail.label: Lower Lake Stone Jail
Lower Lake Stone Jail.description: Lower Lake Stone Jail, in Lower Lake, California, claimed to be the smallest jail in the United States, was erected in 1876 of stone locally quarried and reinforced with iron. Wikipedia

Mary Washington House.label: Mary Washington House
Mary Washington House.description: The Mary Washington House, at 1200 Charles Street in Fredericksburg, Virginia, is the house in which George Washington's mother, Mary Ball Washington, resided towards the end of her life. Wikipedia

Maitland Art Center.label: Maitland Art Center
Maitland Art Center.description: The Maitland Art Center is a historic site in Maitland, Florida. It was founded and designed by architect and artist J. Andre Smith in 1937. It is located at 231 West Packwood Avenue. Wikipedia

Marian Fell Library.label: Marian Fell Library
Marian Fell Library.description: The Marian Fell Library is an historic library in Fellsmere, Florida. It is located 63 North Cypress Street. On October 8, 1996, it was added to the U.S. National Register of Historic Places. Wikipedia

Milwaukee County Courthouse.label: Milwaukee County Courthouse
Milwaukee County Courthouse.description: The Milwaukee County Courthouse is a high-rise municipal building located in downtown Milwaukee, Wisconsin. Completed in 1931, it is the third county courthouse built in the city and is listed on the National Register of Historic Places. Wikipedia

Mariners House.label: Mariners House
Mariners House.description:
Mariner's House is a historic hotel at 11 North Square in Boston, Massachusetts.
It was built in 1847 by the Boston Port and Seamen's Aid Society as an inexpensive hotel for merchant mariners on active duty. It maintains that role today. Wikipedia

National Hotel (Cuylerville, New York).label: National Hotel
National Hotel (Cuylerville, New York).description: National Hotel is a historic hotel located at Cuylerville in Livingston County, New York. It is a large 2-story, seven-by-three-bay Federal / Greek Revival–style frame structure. Wikipedia

New Slains Castle.label: New Slains Castle
New Slains Castle.description: Slains Castle, also known as New Slains Castle to distinguish it from nearby Old Slains Castle, is a ruined castle in Aberdeenshire, Scotland. It overlooks the North Sea from its cliff-top site 1 kilometre east of Cruden Bay. Wikipedia

Mid-South Coliseum.label: Mid-South Coliseum
Mid-South Coliseum.description: The Mid-South Coliseum, also known as "The Entertainment Capital of the Mid-South", was a multi-purpose arena, that seated 10,085 people, in Memphis, Tennessee. It was built in 1963 and closed in 2006. Wikipedia

Peleg Arnold Tavern.label: Peleg Arnold Tavern
Peleg Arnold Tavern.description: The Peleg Arnold Tavern off Great Road in Union Village in North Smithfield, Rhode Island was built around 1690 and is one the oldest homes in North Smithfield. Wikipedia

Rippon Lodge.label: Rippon Lodge
Rippon Lodge.description: Rippon Lodge is the oldest house remaining in Prince William County, Virginia. Built around 1747 by Richard Blackburn, it lies on high ground overlooking Neabsco Creek at the south end of what is now ... Wikipedia
Address: 0.8 mi. N of jct. of U.S. 1 and VA 642

Ron George Round Barn.label: Ron George Round Barn
Ron George Round Barn.description: Ron George Round Barn is a round barn northeast of the U.S. village of Romeoville, Illinois. It was originally constructed for Frank Eaton c. 1912–13 in Bolingbrook, Illinois. Wikipedia

The Wayside.label: The Wayside
The Wayside.description: The Wayside is a historic house in Concord, Massachusetts. The earliest part of the home may date to 1717. Wikipedia

Thomas Law House.label: Thomas Law House
Thomas Law House.description:
The Thomas Law House was built in 1795 near present day 6th and N Streets, Southwest in Washington, D.C. The builder was James Greenleaf, an early land speculator in the District of Columbia.
The mansion was built by Greenleaf for Thomas Law. Wikipedia

Wadsworth-Longfellow House.label: Wadsworth-Longfellow House
Wadsworth-Longfellow House.description: The Wadsworth-Longfellow House is an historic house and museum in Portland, Maine, United States. It is located at 489 Congress Street and is operated by the Maine Historical Society. Wikipedia

William L. Slayton House.label: William L. Slayton House
William L. Slayton House.description: The William L. Slayton House located in the Cleveland Park neighborhood in Washington, D.C., is a house that was designed by I.M. Pei in the International Style. Wikipedia

Wye Mill.label: Wye Mill
Wye Mill.description: The Wye Mill is a historic grist mill located at Wye Mills, Queen Anne's County, Maryland, United States. It is one of the earliest industrial sites on the Eastern Shore in continuous use; dating to the mid 18th century. Wikipedia

Castle of Aguas Mansas.label: Castle of Aguas Mansas
Castle of Aguas Mansas.description: The Castle of Aguas Mansas is a castle located in Agoncillo, Spain. It was declared Bien de Interés Cultural in 1983. Wikipedia

Ljubljana Cathedral.label: Ljubljana Cathedral
Ljubljana Cathedral.description: Ljubljana Cathedral, also named Saint Nicholas' Church, Saint Nicholas' Cathedral, the Cathedral of Saint Nicholas, or simply the Cathedral, is a cathedral in Ljubljana, the capital of Slovenia. Originally, Ljubljana Cathedral was a Gothic church. Wikipedia

Chapel of Luis de Lucena.label: Chapel of Luis de Lucena
Chapel of Luis de Lucena.description: The Chapel of Luis de Lucena is a chapel located in Guadalajara, Spain. It was declared Bien de Interés Cultural in 1914. Wikipedia

Mysore Palace.label: Amba Vilas Palace
Mysore Palace.description: The Palace of Mysore is a historical palace situated in the city of Mysore in Karnataka, southern India. It is the official residence of the Wodeyars, the former royal family of Mysore, which ruled the princely state of Mysore from 1399 to 1947. Wikipedia

National Pantheon of the Dominican Repub.label: National Pantheon of the Dominican Republic
National Pantheon of the Dominican Repub.description: The National Pantheon was built from 1714-1746 by the Spaniard Geronimo Quezada y Garçon and was originally a Jesuit church. The structure was constructed in the neoclassic-renaissance style. Wikipedia

San Marcos de Apalache Historic State Pa.label: San Marcos de Apalache Historic State Park
San Marcos de Apalache Historic State Pa.description: San Marcos de Apalache Historic State Park is a Florida State Park and historic site located in Wakulla County, Florida. It is located in St. Marks, off S.R. 363. The address is 148 Old Fort Road. Wikipedia

Santa Cruz Palace, Madrid.label: Santa Cruz Palace, Madrid
Santa Cruz Palace, Madrid.description: The Palacio de Santa Cruz or Palace of the Holy Cross is a baroque building in central Madrid, Spain. It now houses the foreign ministry or Ministerio de Asuntos Exteriores de España. Wikipedia
Santa Cruz Palace, Madrid.Address: Plaza de Santa Cruz, 6, 28012 Madrid, Spain

Temple of Eshmun.label: Temple of Eshmun
Temple of Eshmun.description: The Temple of Eshmun is an ancient place of worship dedicated to Eshmun, the Phoenician god of healing. It is located near the Awali river, 2 kilometres northeast of Sidon in southwestern Lebanon. Wikipedia

Church of Nuestra Señora de la Asunción.label: Church of Nuestra Señora de la Asunción
Church of Nuestra Señora de la Asunción.description: The Church of Nuestra Señora de la Asunción is a church located in Meco, Spain. It was declared Bien de Interés Cultural 1982. Wikipedia
Church of Nuestra Señora de la Asunción.Address: Plaza de Ramón y Cajal, 2, 28880 Meco, Madrid, Spain

Heath Wood barrow cemetery.label: Heath Wood barrow cemetery
Heath Wood barrow cemetery.description: Heath Wood barrow cemetery is a Viking burial site near Ingleby, Derbyshire. Wikipedia

Aga Khan Palace.label: Aga Khan Palace
Aga Khan Palace.description: The Aga Khan Palace was built by Sultan Muhammed Shah Aga Khan III in Pune, India. Built in 1892, it is one of the biggest landmarks in Indian history. Wikipedia

Church of St Luke and St Andrew, Priston.label: Church of St Luke and St Andrew, Priston
Church of St Luke and St Andrew, Priston.description: The Church of St Luke and St Andrew in Priston, Somerset, England has a nave dating from the 12th century, on the site of an earlier Norman church. It has been designated as a Grade I listed building. Wikipedia

Hastings Fishermen's Museum.label: Hastings Fishermen's Museum
Hastings Fishermen's Museum.description: Hastings Fishermen's Museum is a museum dedicated to the fishing industry and maritime history of Hastings, a seaside town in East Sussex, England. Wikipedia

Duchal House.label: Duchal House
Duchal House.description: Duchal House is an 18th-century mansion and estate near Kilmacolm, Scotland. It is located in Inverclyde, in the former county of Renfrewshire. Duchal was acquired by the Porterfield family in the 16th century. Wikipedia

House of Hermanitas de los Pobres.label: House of Hermanitas de los Pobres
House of Hermanitas de los Pobres.description: The House of Hermanitas de los Pobres is a building located in Madrid, Spain. It was declared Bien de Interés Cultural in 1996. Wikipedia

Kilmory Castle.label: Kilmory Castle
Kilmory Castle.description: Kilmory Castle, also known as Kilmory House, is a large 19th-century house located just to the south of Lochgilphead, in Argyll, Argyll and Bute, on the west coast of Scotland. It is currently occupied by the headquarters of Argyll and Bute Council. Wikipedia

Lord Leycester Hospital.label: Lord Leycester Hospital
Lord Leycester Hospital.description: The Lord Leycester Hospital is a retirement home for ex-Servicemen in Warwick, England, that is located next to the West Gate, on High Street. Wikipedia

Monument to the Restorers.label: Monument to the Restorers
Monument to the Restorers.description: The Monument to the Restorers is a monument located in Restauradores Square in Lisbon, Portugal. The monument was designed by António Tomás da Fonseca and erected in 1886. Wikipedia

Mormon Pioneer Memorial Monument.label: Mormon Pioneer Memorial Monument
Mormon Pioneer Memorial Monument.description: The Mormon Pioneer Memorial Monument is a private cemetery and memorial. It was dedicated to the more than 6,000 Mormon pioneers who died making the journey to Utah from Illinois and other parts of the world between 1847 and 1869. Wikipedia

Peteetneet Museum and Cultural Arts Cent.label: Peteetneet School
Peteetneet Museum and Cultural Arts Cent.description: The Peteetneet Museum and Cultural Arts Center, located in Payson, Utah, is named after Ute Chief Peteetneet and serves multiple civic purposes. Wikipedia

All Saints Church, Idmiston.label: All Saints Church, Idmiston
All Saints Church, Idmiston.description: All Saints Church in Idmiston, Wiltshire, England, was built in the 12th century. It is designated by English Heritage as a Grade I listed building, and is a redundant church in the care of the Churches Conservation Trust. Wikipedia

Royal Academy of Pharmacy.label: Royal Academy of Pharmacy
Royal Academy of Pharmacy.description: The Real Academia Nacional de Farmacia is located in Madrid, Spain. It was declared Bien de Interés Cultural in 1997. Wikipedia
